stimulus:
In this task, you will see a series of objects. On some trials, your job is to determine whether the object shown is a color photograph or a line drawing. On other trials, your job is to determine whether the object represented is animate or inanimate.

You will know which response to make depending on the initial display, which will say "animate / inanimate" or "photo / drawing".

You will be able to use the left arrow key to report animate/photo and the right arrow key to report inanimate/drawing.
Please respond as quickly as possible, and use your dominant hand to make your responses.


In the example in the top row, the correct response is animate (left arrow key). In the example in the bottom row, the correct response is photo (left arrow key).

You will first do some practice trials. When you are ready to begin, press the space bar.

Great job! Now you'll continue onto doing the main task. You will have the opportunity to take brief breaks at various points. Good luck!
Press the space bar to continue.
